OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1777986670
OL,3,CUrgent action taken to remove trees
OL,4,Cinfected with Ash Dieback from woodland
OL,6,F"With no treatments to help save
OL,7,Faffected trees, once a tree has ash
OL,8,Fdieback it will stop growing any new
OL,9,Fbranches and what remains will die off
OL,10,Fand become unsafe.
OL,12,FThe local authority has been
OL,13,Fmonitoring the spread of ash dieback
OL,14,Fin the borough, through routine
OL,15,Finspections. During the work a
OL,16,Fqualified ecologist will be on site to
OL,17,Fadvise on the pruning works to help
OL,18,Freduce the likelihood of harming
OL,19,Fwildlife.
OL,26,@nD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/5
